Cell.Text: How does anyone expect me to write my opus with all of these rude interruptions?

Cell.Text: "What do I mean," indeed! | If I hadn't lost all of the pages, I wouldn't be in this predicament and we wouldn't be having this conversation.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQSaintIntroBranchTopic01: Opus? What do you mean?

Cell.Text: Very well. I suppose a moment or two of my time couldn't hurt. | I am Jiub. Some call me Saint Jiub. Others call me Jiub the Eradicator. Perhaps you've heard of me?

Node.Caption: DLC1VQSaintIntroBranchTopic02: Let's just start at the beginning...

Cell.Text: [S] G|And you think I do? Humph.
[S] G|Oh, this is simply getting infuriating!

Node.Caption: DLC1VQSaintIntroBranchTopic02a: I don't have time for this.

Cell.Text: Oh, I see. You've decided to cease pursuing your busy schedule and wish to talk now. How kind.
[S] I can't say that I'm surprised by your answer. Until I get my second volume published, no one will ever know of my achievements.
A book? I'd hardly call a twenty-six volume epic simply a "book." | Surely you've heard of "The Rise and Fall of Saint Jiub the Eradicator: Hero of Morrowind and Savior of the Dunmer."
Maybe you should leave the writing to an expert and stop making foolish suggestions.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQSaintMainBranchTopic01: Maybe a shorter title is in order?

Cell.Text: Terrible, simply terrible. | I was in the midst of writing the second volume and they just threw me into this prison. It's unfair!

Node.Caption: DLC1VQSaintMainBranchTopic02: How is your work going so far?

Cell.Text: [S] That damn dremora and his minions. They didn't even give me a chance to explain who I was.
[S] Soul what? What in the name of Vivec are you talking about? | All I remember is that damn dremora and his minions bursting into my home and sending me to their prison.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQSaintMainBranchTopic04: Prison? You mean the Soul Cairn?

Cell.Text: Well, I assume so. It cast a spell at me from some kind of strange black crystal. | Next thing I knew, I arrived here.
[S] Hmph. I tell you what's crazy. | How about sitting in your home, minding your own business and then suddenly getting attacked by a dremora and his cronies.
No... all these wasted months, or has it been years? I don't even remember how much time has passed. | Now my work will never see the light of day. My name will be forgotten.
Perhaps. Do you have a way out of here?
Maybe I can't leave, but my writings can. | In order to write the second volume of my opus, I need the notes from my first volume. Otherwise I need to do all of this from memory.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQSaintSecondBranchTopic04: I do, but you can't leave that way.

Cell.Text: [S] When I was tossed in here I felt myself falling... and I dropped the pages I had been holding. | There were ten of them in all. Find them for me, please, I beg you!

Node.Caption: DLC1VQSaintSecondBranchTopic05: How many pages did you lose?
